POST /attempts records a sessionless attempt (Today inline recall — sessionId
was already nullable) and PATCH /attempts/:id carries the post-reveal half of
plan §7.2's lifecycle: rate + reflect after the reference answer is on screen.
Both schedule FSRS reviews on rating with the same non-fatal contract as
sessions.answer. answerText is deliberately immutable on PATCH — the attempt
records what was recalled before the reveal.
