 =?UTF-8?q?=E2=86=92=20rate=20session=20lifecycle=20(plan=20=C2=A77.2)?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The session flow asked for self-rating and miss-tags before the reference
answer was ever shown — and never showed it at all. Rating blind is guessing,
and FSRS scheduled from guesses drifts. AnswerForm is now recall-only; the new
RevealPanel carries everything after submit: reference answer, rubric, the
user's answer side-by-side, reflection (moved here, where 'what did I miss' is
answerable), labeled Again/Hard/Good/Easy grading via PATCH /attempts/:id, and
the existing AiFeedbackCard. Answered questions reopen in their reveal (keyed
remount per attempt); ReviewQuestionCard deleted as superseded. Summary gains
collapsible reference answers, grade chips, and 'Retry N missed' via a
questionIds-pinned session.
