Subject: [PATCH 5/6] feat(web): Today reviews become real recall practice;
 weakness repair entry points
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Today's 'Review now' expanded into bare 1-5 buttons — a grade with no prompt,
no recall attempt, no reveal. TodayReviewCard now runs the loop inline:
expand → prompt → optional typed recall → reveal → Again/Hard/Good/Easy. A
typed recall posts a real standalone attempt (streak/history/weakness signals
all count it); a mental-only recall records just the grade. Practice hub shows
live weak spots from GET /weaknesses with a one-tap repair session; the
weak_area_review description now matches what it actually does.
